This is a temporary fix for CM9 ICS 4.0.4 [tested it with acer iconia a500]

How to patch & Build

Set up repo
$ mkdir ~/bin
$ PATH=~/bin:$PATH
$ curl https://dl-ssl.google.com/dl/googlesource/git-repo/repo > ~/bin/repo
$ chmod a+x ~/bin/repo

Download CM9 source
$ mkdir ~/CM9_4.0.4
$ cd ~/CM9_4.0.4
$ repo init -u git://github.com/CyanogenMod/android.git -b ics
$ repo sync

Download Cornerstone form my repo
$ git clone git://github.com/pjsports/cornerstone.git
$ cd ~/cornerstone
$ git pull

Merg the directories
$ rsync -a cornerstone/ CM9_4.0.4/ --exclude='.git*'

Build & Compile
$ cd ~/CM9_4.0.4
$ . build/envsetup.sh && brunch your_devices

Download ROM CM9 4.0.4 for ACER Iconia A500
-

Thanks to 
- Cornerstone project https://github.com/Onskreen/cornerstone
- waydownsouth https://github.com/waydownsouth



